hpnicfDot11sMesh.name: hpnicfDot11sMesh

revisions.description: Modified to add new nodes and a new table.
The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfDot11sMesh.description: The file defines a MIB to provide MESH configuration information. GLOSSARY IEEE 802.11 Standard to encourage interoperability among wireless networking equipment. Access point (AP) Transmitter/receiver (transceiver) device that commonly connects and transports data between a wireless network and a wired network. Access control (AC) To control and manage multi-APs, it will bridge wireless and wired network. Fat AP Applied in the home, SOHO and so on, and it could work independently without help from AC. Fit AP Applied in the enterprise environment, it will work under the control and management from AC. BSS IEEE 802.11 Basic Service Set (Radio Cell). The BSS of an AP comprises of the stations directly associating with the AP. Radio The chip set to receive and send wireless signal. Mesh A network consisting of two or more mesh points which communicate with each other via mesh services. Mesh Point (MP) An IEEE 802.11 entity that contains an IEEE 802.11-conformant medium access control (MAC) and physical layer (PHY) interface to the wireless medium (WM) that supports mesh services. Mesh Access Point (MAP) A mesh point that is collocated with one or more access points. Mesh Portal Point (MPP) A mesh point that is collocated with one or more portals. Mesh Link A link between two MPs.

hpnicfDot11sMeshMkdID.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshMkdID
hpnicfDot11sMeshMkdID.description: This object represents the mesh key distributor identifier (MKD-ID). If the MKD-ID is not configured, the value is '00:00:00:00:00:00'.

hpnicfDot11sMeshPflTable.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshPflTable
hpnicfDot11sMeshPflTable.description: This table is used to configure mesh profile. A mesh profile is created and mapped to a MP so that it can provide mesh services to other MPs which have the same mesh ID. When the mesh profile is enabled, all of the object in this table can not be modified except hpnicfDot11sMeshPflEnable. The mesh profile can not be deleted when it is bound with the radio.

hpnicfDot11sMeshPflEntry.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshPflEntry
hpnicfDot11sMeshPflEntry.description: Each entry contains information of a mesh profile.

hpnicfDot11sMeshPflIndex.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshPflIndex
hpnicfDot11sMeshPflIndex.description: This object represents the index of the mesh profile.

hpnicfDot11sMeshPflMeshID.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshPflMeshID
hpnicfDot11sMeshPflMeshID.description: This object represents the mesh ID of the mesh profile. The string length of this object is zero when the mesh ID is not configured. If the mesh ID is not configured, hpnicfDot11sMeshPflEnable can not be set to 'true'.

hpnicfDot11sMeshPflBindIntNum.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshPflBindIntNum
hpnicfDot11sMeshPflBindIntNum.description: This object represents the specified mesh interface number binding to the mesh profile. If the value is set to -1, the binding will be removed. If the mesh interface is not specified, the value of hpnicfDot11sMeshPflEnable can not be set to 'true'.

hpnicfDot11sMeshPflKeepAlive.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshPflKeepAlive
hpnicfDot11sMeshPflKeepAlive.description: This object represents the mesh link keep-alive interval.

hpnicfDot11sMeshPflBackhaulRate.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshPflBackhaulRate
hpnicfDot11sMeshPflBackhaulRate.description: This object represents the link backhaul rate.

hpnicfDot11sMeshMkdServEnable.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshMkdServEnable
hpnicfDot11sMeshMkdServEnable.description: This object indicates whether the mesh key distributor (MKD) service for the mesh profile is enabled. 'true': The MKD service for the mesh profile is enabled. 'false': The MKD service for the mesh profile is disabled.

hpnicfDot11sMeshPflEnable.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshPflEnable
hpnicfDot11sMeshPflEnable.description: This object indicates whether the mesh profile is enabled. 'true': The mesh profile is enabled. 'false': The mesh profile is disabled.

hpnicfDot11sMeshPflRowStatus.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshPflRowStatus
hpnicfDot11sMeshPflRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyTable.name: hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyTable
hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyTable.description: This table is used to configure MP policy. There is 'default_mp_plcy' on system by default and its index is 1. The 'default_mp_plcy' can not be deleted or modified. The MP policy can not be deleted when it is applied to a radio. It can not be modified when it is applied to an enabled radio.

hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyEntry.name: hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyEntry
hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyEntry.description: Each entry contains information of a MP policy.

hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyIndex.name: hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyIndex
hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyIndex.description: This object represents the MP policy index.

hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyName.name: hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyName
hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyName.description: This object represents the MP policy name. MP policy can not be created with name 'a', 'al', 'all' or 'default_mp_plcy'. Modification is not supported.

hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyInitEnable.name: hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyInitEnable
hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyInitEnable.description: This object indicates whether the link initiation for the MP policy is enabled. 'true': The link initiation for the MP policy is enabled. 'false': The link initiation for the MP policy is disabled.

hpnicfDot11sMlspEnable.name: hpnicfDot11sMlspEnable
hpnicfDot11sMlspEnable.description: This object indicates whether the mesh link switch protocol (MLSP) is enabled. 'true': MLSP is enabled. 'false': MLSP is disabled.

hpnicfDot11sProbReqInterval.name: hpnicfDot11sProbReqInterval
hpnicfDot11sProbReqInterval.description: This object represents the probe request interval.

hpnicfDot11sRoleAuthEnable.name: hpnicfDot11sRoleAuthEnable
hpnicfDot11sRoleAuthEnable.description: This object indicates whether the device can play as the role of an authenticator.

hpnicfDot11sLinkHoldRSSI.name: hpnicfDot11sLinkHoldRSSI
hpnicfDot11sLinkHoldRSSI.description: This object represents the link-hold receive signal strength indicator (RSSI).

hpnicfDot11sLinkHoldTime.name: hpnicfDot11sLinkHoldTime
hpnicfDot11sLinkHoldTime.description: This object represents the link-hold time.

hpnicfDot11sSwitchMargin.name: hpnicfDot11sSwitchMargin
hpnicfDot11sSwitchMargin.description: This object represents the link-switch margin.

hpnicfDot11sLinkSaturationRSSI.name: hpnicfDot11sLinkSaturationRSSI
hpnicfDot11sLinkSaturationRSSI.description: This object represents the link saturation receive signal strength indicator (RSSI).

hpnicfDot11sLinkRateMode.name: hpnicfDot11sLinkRateMode
hpnicfDot11sLinkRateMode.description: This object represents the rate mode of the mesh link.

hpnicfDot11sMaxLinkNum.name: hpnicfDot11sMaxLinkNum
hpnicfDot11sMaxLinkNum.description: This object represents the maximum number of the mesh link.

hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyRowStatus.name: hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyRowStatus
hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfDot11sMlspCfgTable.name: hpnicfDot11sMlspCfgTable
hpnicfDot11sMlspCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure MLSP proxy MAC address. Only if the specified MP policy is modifiable and the MLSP is enabled, the row of this table can be created and deleted. The row of this table can not be modified.

hpnicfDot11sMlspCfgEntry.name: hpnicfDot11sMlspCfgEntry
hpnicfDot11sMlspCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains information of MLSP proxy MAC address.

hpnicfDot11sMlspProxyIndex.name: hpnicfDot11sMlspProxyIndex
hpnicfDot11sMlspProxyIndex.description: This object represents the MLSP proxy MAC address index.

hpnicfDot11sMlspProxyMac.name: hpnicfDot11sMlspProxyMac
hpnicfDot11sMlspProxyMac.description: This object represents the MLSP proxy MAC address.

hpnicfDot11sMlspRowStatus.name: hpnicfDot11sMlspRowStatus
hpnicfDot11sMlspRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfDot11sRadioCfgTable.name: hpnicfDot11sRadioCfgTable
hpnicfDot11sRadioCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure mesh to the specified radio.

hpnicfDot11sRadioCfgEntry.name: hpnicfDot11sRadioCfgEntry
hpnicfDot11sRadioCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains mesh configure information of the specified radio.

hpnicfDot11sMeshPflMap.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshPflMap
hpnicfDot11sMeshPflMap.description: This object represents the number of the mesh profile mapped to the specified radio. The value is zero when the radio is not binding mesh profile.

hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyMap.name: hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyMap
hpnicfDot11sMpPlcyMap.description: This object represents the index of the MP policy mapped to the specified radio. The MP policy is 'default_mp_plcy' when the radio is not binding user-defined MP policy. The index of 'default_mp_plcy' is 1. This object can not be modified when the radio is enabled.

hpnicfDot11sAPCfgTable.name: hpnicfDot11sAPCfgTable
hpnicfDot11sAPCfgTable.description: This table is used to configure mesh to the specified AP.

hpnicfDot11sAPCfgEntry.name: hpnicfDot11sAPCfgEntry
hpnicfDot11sAPCfgEntry.description: Each entry contains mesh configure information of the specified AP.

hpnicfDot11sPortalEnable.name: hpnicfDot11sPortalEnable
hpnicfDot11sPortalEnable.description: This object indicates whether the portal service is enabled. 'true': The portal service is enabled. 'false': The portal service is disabled.

hpnicfDot11sWDSPeerMacTable.name: hpnicfDot11sWDSPeerMacTable
hpnicfDot11sWDSPeerMacTable.description: This table is used to configure wireless distribution system (WDS). The row of this table can not be modified.

hpnicfDot11sWDSPeerMacEntry.description: Each entry contains information of WDS.

hpnicfDot11sWDSPeerMacIndex.name: hpnicfDot11sWDSPeerMacIndex

hpnicfDot11sWDSPeerMacRowStatus.name: hpnicfDot11sWDSPeerMacRowStatus
hpnicfDot11sWDSPeerMacRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

hpnicfDot11sMeshLinkIfIndex.name: hpnicfDot11sMeshLinkIfIndex
